DEst1 was further tested in combination with each of 10 pairs of primers for CHIKV detection for compatibility and capability of differentiating DENV from CHIKV. The pair of DEst1 and CHK1 (Figure 2
) (the specific Tm of CHIKV PCR amplicon was 88.28°C, with coefficient of variation of 0.46%) was selected because not only was it able to detect DENV and CHIKV but also it had a similar annealing temperature and low tendency of forming heterodimers. The results for the combination of DEst1 and CHK1 revealed good consistency compared with use of DEst1 alone, in terms of specific Tms of amplicons from DENV-1, -2, -3, and -4. Figure 3
lists the temperature ranges for the PCR amplicons specific to each DENV serotype and CHIKV.
